      <h2>Text Hithlighting Example</h2>
      <p>A paragraph is a group of <mark>sentences or a single</mark> sentence that forms a distinct unit of writing, focusing on a single, cohesive idea or topic. Typically, it begins with a topic sentence, followed by supporting sentences that provide details or examples, and often concludes by summarizing the main point. It acts as a visual and conceptual break in text, usually marked by an indentation or a line break. </p>
<h2>Using Small tags</h2>
<p>Supporting Sentences: Provide evidence, <small>examples,</small> or details that develop the topic sentence.
</p>
